<HEAD>Fires Kill and Injure 60,000 Chinese in Past Decade</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Chinese have died in fires at a rate of seven per day over the past decade, an official newspaper reported today. The <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> Daily said 410,000 fires killed or injured 60,000 people and caused $ 784 million in damage over the past 10 years. The report did not give a figure for deaths, but at seven fatalities a day the total would be about 25,000. The daily, quoting the <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION>'s fire control department, said the majority of fires are caused by human error, negligence and failure to carry out fire safety measures. One-third of fires are a result of faulty electrical wiring in buildings, it said, and senior officials of enterprises hit by fires are rarely punished. The daily also quoted <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> fire officials as saying their communications and fire-fighting equipment are outdated.
