<TEXT>
 Four people, including a teen-ager shopping for Christmas gifts, were killed and 13 were wounded over the weekend in attacks police linked to gang violence. A 15-year-old boy was killed Sunday night in <LOCATION> Hawaiian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gardens </LOCATION>, about 20 miles southeast of downtown. The teen-ager, who was not identified pending notification of relatives, was standing on a sidewalk when a car with five males stopped and yelled to him, police Deputy <PERSON> Chris </PERSON> <PERSON> Wahla </PERSON> said. When the youth approached the car, he was shot with a shotgun, <PERSON> Wahla </PERSON> said. He was pronounced dead at a hospital. Earlier Sunday, a man bearing gang tattoos was stabbed to death in <LOCATION> Pacoima </LOCATION>, an unincorporated area 20 miles northwest of downtown in the <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Fernando </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>. Detectives said the victim's attackers escaped. Two alleged gang members were booked for investigation of murder after a teen-age bystander was killed in a gang shooting inside a crowded shopping mall in <LOCATION> Panorama </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, police said. <PERSON> Sergio </PERSON> <PERSON> Alpuche </PERSON>, 16, of <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> Nuys </PERSON>, who was not known to be a gang member, was hit by a bullet in the chest Friday while shopping for Christmas presents in the <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Fernando </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION> mall. He died the next day. Arrested in the shooting were two young men, ages 22 and 18, both believed to be gang members. Also arrested was a 16-year-old, police said. The fourth gang killing occurred Friday night when <PERSON> Terrance </PERSON> <PERSON> Carl </PERSON> <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON>, 27, of <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> was gunned down by rival gang members as he walked with his girlfriend. She was unhurt. Two gang members were wounded by riv