<ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> officials said. The cultural pact includes a program for student exchanges for the first time, they said. <PERSON> Shevardnadze </PERSON>'s wife <PERSON> Nanuli </PERSON>, who is a journalist, will attend various cultural activities, including a tea ceremony, during her stay. She is to visit a pearl shop, museum and library and meet <PERSON> Hanae </PERSON> <PERSON> Mori </PERSON>, one of <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s top fashion designers. <PERSON> Shevardnadze </PERSON> is to leave <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> Wednesday for the <LOCATION> Philippines </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>.
