<HEAD>Woman Scares Away Assailant With Punch-And-Kick Combination</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NORTH LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 51-year-old fashion model says she scared away an armed assailant with a rib punch and a kick to the shins because she did n't want to die. <PERSON> Carolyn </PERSON> <PERSON> Brimer </PERSON> said she left the pistol-packing man stunned Saturday after he assaulted her in a shopping mall parking lot. `` I did n't want to be lying in a ditch, bleeding to death,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Brimer </PERSON> said. `` I did n't want to be dead in a gutter.'' Mrs. <PERSON> Brimer </PERSON>, 5-foot-5 and 115 pounds, was on her way to her job as a department store model when a man appeared as she was getting her purse from her car. The man jabbed a pistol into her rib cage and told her to get into her car, Mrs. <PERSON> Brimer </PERSON> said. `` I knew if I got in that car, that was it,'' she said. She said she shouted `` No!'' and gave the man the one-two, punch-kick combination. The man looked stunned, then slowly walked away with his head cocked to one side, still looking at her. Mrs. <PERSON> Brimer </PERSON> jumped into her car and locked the doors. <PERSON> Larry </PERSON> <PERSON> Epperson </PERSON>, an off-duty policeman working as a mall security guard, then walked by and offered help. <PERSON> Epperson </PERSON> took Mrs. <PERSON> Brimer </PERSON> inside the store and then chased a man on foot and apprehended him. No weapon was found. Police charged <PERSON> Billy </PERSON> <PERSON> Terry </PERSON>, 23, of <PERSON> Atkins </PERSON>, with criminal attempt to commit kidnapping, aggravated assault and fleeing the scene of a crime. `` I'm just thankful I have my life _ that <PERSON> God </PERSON> had his hand in it,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Brimer </PERSON> said. `` I hope other women will stand up and fight. Someone has got to put a stop to this.''
