<HEAD>AP WEEKEND ENTERTAINMENT AND ARTS</HEAD>
<HEAD>Star Watch: TV Villain Makes Good on Big Screen</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BOB THOMAS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The strangest hit of the holiday season is a gag-packed feature version of a television series that lasted only four weeks, starring an actor better known for playing villains than getting laughs. <PERSON> Leslie </PERSON> <PERSON> Nielsen </PERSON>, who has a long record of evil-doing in films and television, is currently killing people with laughs in `` The Naked Gun: From the Files of Police Squad!'' The Paramount Pictures release is the work of <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Zucker </PERSON>, <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Abrams </PERSON> and <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Zucker </PERSON>, who previously made `` Airplane!'' and who specialize in titles and scripts with exclamation marks. <PERSON> Nielsen </PERSON>, 62, repeats the role of Lt. <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Drebin </PERSON>, the incredibly incompetent detective who appeared in the brief, lamented 1982 series `` Police Squad!'' The actor, who had appeared in `` Airplane!,'' recalled the inception of the show: `` <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> and <PERSON> David </PERSON> invited me to lunch, and they even pitched me! They did n't realize I was putty in their hands. Anything they wanted me to do, I was willing. `` They mentioned doing ` Police Squad' on television. Can you imagine me doing Lt. <PERSON> Drebin </PERSON> on TV under the auspices of the <ORGANIZATION> Zuckers </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Abrams </PERSON>? Paradise!'' Sad to say, <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> yanked `` Police Squad!'' after six chapters were made and four aired. Why? `` It did n't belong on TV,'' <PERSON> Nielsen </PERSON> theorized. `` It had the kind of humor you have to pay attention to. When you have a screen that is bigger than life, you can see what is going on in the background. You do n't have to search for it. `` You can watch it at home and look around and say, ` Gee, I'm going to get that door painted,' or ` Leave the telephone alone. There was no laugh track to bring the audience's attention back to the screen. It belongs up there on the big screen, -LRB- in theaters -RRB- where people have paid money to get in so they're not liable to waste their money by not paying attention.'' <PERSON> Nielsen </PERSON> explained that <ORGANIZATION> ZAZ </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- as the trio are called -RRB- originally planned to make a feature of `` Police Squad!'' but could n't find a plot long enough. So they fashioned mini-plots for a TV series. After years of trying, they came up with a story that pitted <PERSON> Drebin </PERSON> against <PERSON> Vincent </PERSON> <PERSON> Ludwig </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Ricardo </PERSON> <PERSON> Mantalban </PERSON> -RRB-, the <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> businessman who is really a killer. A large part of the appeal of `` Naked Gun-Police Squad'' can be attributed to <PERSON> Nielsen </PERSON>'s straight-arrow playing of the outrageous events. There is a certain madness in his method: `` The more seriousness, the more credibility you present in your demeanor when you're talking about insanity, the funnier it becomes.'' Although he was something of a practical joker as a boy in <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Norman </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Saskatchewan </LOCATION> -LRB- `` We did n't know that water bombs would freeze on the way down from a second-story window'' -RRB-, <PERSON> Leslie </PERSON> <PERSON> Nielsen </PERSON> was not considered much of a comedian in his early years. One of three sons of a <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Canadian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mountie </ORGANIZATION>, he served as a gunner in the <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Canadian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> and later studied at <PERSON> Lorne </PERSON> <PERSON> Greene </PERSON>'s radio academy in <LOCATION> Toronto </LOCATION>. Winning a scholarship to <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Y