dustry says fears of genetically engineered bacteria running wild mislead the public and legislators into seeking to toughen the regulatory road. Big companies have the experience and financial strength to deal with regulatory delays, but smaller companies feel the pressure. They can no longer ask investors to wait as in the early days of biotechnology.
