<HEAD>London Shares Slightly Lower At Midday</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: will be led after closing</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices fell slightly in light trading at midday Monday, as investors began to turn their attention toward the upcoming holidays and Friday's release of British trade figures for November. The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was off 0.3 point, or 0.02 percent, at 1,773.4 around 12:30 p.m. local time, below its early morning peak of 1,779.0. Volume was a light 192.5 million shares, compared with 235.8 million shares at the same time Friday. `` It certainly feels a lot like Christmas week,'' one trader said. `` We've seen modest waves of interest throughout the morning but absolutely no follow-through.'' Dealers said the Friday release of the British trade report likely would keep players anxious and sidelined during the coming week.
