<HEAD>Icahn Ups Stake in Texaco Again</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: SUBS 5th graf to UPDATE with Texaco declining comment; picks
up 6th graf pvs bg'ng, In New ...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Takeover strategist <PERSON> Carl </PERSON> <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> has purchased another 1 million shares of <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, raising his stake to 16.22 percent of the third-largest <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> oil company, <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> disclosed Monday. In a routine filing with the <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> also included a letter addressed to <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION>'s president <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Kinnear </PERSON> in which <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> denied rumors of improperly acting in concert with an unidentified investor to acquire <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> stock. <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> is <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION>'s largest single stockholder. `` I've read with interest newspaper reports that unnamed <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> officials have been speculating that I may be acting with another investor or partner in connection with my <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> holdings,'' <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> told <PERSON> Kinnear </PERSON>. `` While I think it is inappropriate for any <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> official to use the newspapers as a forum to speculate on my intentions, I will nevertheless respond and tell you I am not acting with any partner or other undisclosed person with respect to my <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> holdings.'' <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Maneri </PERSON>, at the company's <LOCATION> White </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Plains </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>, office, said <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> customarily declined comment on purchases of its stock. In <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> trading Monday, <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> rose 75 cents a share to $ 51.37 -LCB-. <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> said in the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> filing that he holds 39.67 million <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> shares, including the 1 million purchased from Dec. 13 to Dec. 14 for prices ranging from $ 51.37 -LCB- to $ 52.37 -LCB-. He gave no reason for increasing the stake. <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> has been increasing his pressure on <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> in recent weeks, raising speculation he might resurrect a failed takeover bid for the company, the largest <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> oil concern behind <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Mobil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. Last week, <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> stoked the rumors by disclosing he had purchased 2.6 million shares in early December for an average of $ 50.37 -LCB- a share Securities analysts have said <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON>'s moves evidently reflect his impatience at the pace of the company's post-bankruptcy restructuring plan announced earlier this year. That plan has failed to substantially raise the value of <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION>'s 240 million shares outstanding. Last spring, <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> made an offer for <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> valued at $ 14.5 billion, or $ 60 a share, as part of a shareholder proxy fight to oust the company's board. But his strategy was defeated by shareholders loyal to the board. But since then, <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION>'s dismal stock performance has increased the possibility that more shareholders would align themselves with <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> if he undertook another takeover attempt, analysts have said.
