.2 million in fiscal 1988. It averages $ 1 million a year in sales per store, compared to $ 1.5 million for <ORGANIZATION> McDonald </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION>, $ 920,000 for <ORGANIZATION> Hardee </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> and $ 786,000 -LRB- in 1987 -RRB- for <PERSON> Wendy </PERSON>'s. McDonald's total sales for fiscal 1987 were $ 14.3 billion in its more than 10,000 restaurants. <PERSON> Uphoff </PERSON> suggested the new ownership will want to improve Burger King's marketing, in the aftermath of much-criticized campaigns such as the `` Find Herb'' promotion of a few years ago. <PERSON> Jay </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Freedman </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Kidder </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Peabody </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> said to play catch-up with <ORGANIZATION> McDonald </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION>, Burger King must improve consistency. `` Even if you can convince them to come in, if you do n't give them an acceptable visit with consistently speedy service, clean restaurant and restrooms, they're not going to come back,'' <PERSON> Freedman </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Burger </PERSON> <PERSON> King </PERSON>'s competitors said they did n't expect the takeover to have a major impact immediately on their business. `` It's going to take some time. Nothing's going to happen overnight,'' said <PERSON> Dennis </PERSON> <PERSON> Lynch </PERSON>, spokesman for <PERSON> Wendy </PERSON>'s, based in <LOCATION> Dublin </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>. `` Having a new owner will clarify at least who's calling the shots, but that does n't mean there's a strategic plan in place. For <PERSON> Wendy </PERSON>'s, which has been recovering after slipping financially the past two years, <PERSON> Lynch </PERSON> said the confused situation at Burger King has `` given us an opportunity to tell our message positively.'' <PERSON> Hardee </PERSON>'s, based in <LOCATION> Rocky </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Point </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.C. </LOCATION>, has been growing fastest among the industry's leaders, said spokesman <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Singer </PERSON>, and should hold its own against any new Burger King initiatives. From McDonald's <LOCATION> Oak </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Brook </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ill. </LOCATION> headquarters, spokesman <PERSON> Chuck </PERSON> <PERSON> Ebeling </PERSON> said the successful recipe of good service, good value and cleanliness is what the industry leader concerns itself with. `` We do n't talk about our competitors or the industry,'' <PERSON> Ebeling </PERSON> said. `` We speak only of <ORGANIZATION> McDonald </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION>. Just because they change ownership ... they're still Brand X.''
